    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-01T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.24/25a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Farrell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-01T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. The President will announce on May 2 that Iraq has been designated as
                    eligible to receive Lend-Lease assistance.<note n="6" xml:id="d401fn6">For the
                        text of announcement concerning lend-lease aid to both Iraq and Iran, see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, May 2, 1942, p. 383;
                        for correspondence regarding lend-lease aid to Iran, see <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_289">pp. 289</ref> ff.</note> Please inform
                    Iraqi Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
